<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>welcome to the cgi_app demo</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>welcome to the cgi_app demo</h1>
    <p>this is the welcome screen. it is generated by the default run mode
    'welcome'. here are some of the other sample run modes:</p>
    <ul>
    <li><a href="example.cgi?rm=param_example_form">CGI parameters</a></li>
    <li><a href="example.cgi?rm=cookie_example">cookies</a></li>
    <li><a href="example.cgi?rm=redirect_example">a server side redirect to
    google.com</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>the application was setup by subclassing CGI_Application and
    overriding the setup() method with:</p>
    <pre>
    def setup(self):
        self.start_mode = "welcome"
        self._dispatch["welcome"] = self.welcome
        self._dispatch["param_example_form"] = self.param_example_form
        self._dispatch["param_example"] = self.param_example
        self._dispatch["cookie_example"] = self.cookie_example
        self._dispatch["redirect_example"] = self.redirect_example
    </pre>

    <p>the code for this runmode looks like:</p>
    <pre>
    def welcome(self):
        return self.template("welcome.tmpl",{})
    </pre>
    
  </body>
</html>
